events.name: Guest event: League of Geeks Episode #2
events.description:
(This event is not organized by GDG Passau; But it's related and also in Passau)

Please RVSP on eventbrite: https://www.eventbrite.de/e/league-of-geeks-episode-2-tickets-38759516758

<a href="https://www.eventbrite.de/e/league-of-geeks-episode-2-tickets-38759516758"></a>Message

"Minnosphere and synsugar has a new series of presentation.
The first presentation was about progressive web apps and was very awesome.

The next presentation is about GitLab.
Everyone who is interested and wants to get in contact with other developer is
very welcome.

I'm new in the GDG Group and would really enjoy to get in contact with some of you guys."

Abstract

With their consistent release cycle, great openness and breath-taking development speed, GitLab managed to establish themselves as an alternative to top dog GitHub – and not just for being "Open Source". The Service Desk found in the Enterprise Edition tackles ZenDesk, Mattermost is their own implementation of Slack, and basic functionality of tools like Trello or Asana is just integrated into the default feature set. Especially the tightly integrated but easy to configure CI/CD is a darling of the community. Manuel Grabowski, core developer and project lead at mymuesli, gives an introduction to the various possibilities.

events.name: Guest event: League of Geeks - Alexa Skills & Google Assistant Apps
events.description:
(This event is not organized by GDG Passau; But it's related and also in Passau)

Voice is the most natural way to communicate for humans. Voice Assistants are slowly entering our daily life and have the potential to define the next big chapter for user interaction. Assistants are always ready to provide convenient and hands-free guidance for a growing number of tasks.

Stefan Volkmer, Lead IT Consultant at msg systems, will show what’s possible with Voice Assistants and conversational AI. He will introduce Alexa Skill Kit and Google Assistant Dialogflow and compare their capabilities.

Join us for an exciting session about the future of human-computer-interfaces!

RVSP here: https://www.eventbrite.de/e/league-of-geeks-alexa-skills-google-assistant-apps-tickets-42045199323

events.name: DACHFest 2018 (DevFest DACH)
events.description:
For this year's DevFest season, GDG and WTM communities of Germany, Austria, and Switzerland are all working together to organize our largest event yet: DACHFest!

DACHFest is a two-day DevFest conference focused on making a difference. Meet technology experts in emerging fields like AR/VR and Voice UI, discover all the different ways in which technology is transforming lives, find out how to make your apps and websites accessible and friendly towards everyone, learn the secrets of building and nurturing a diverse community — let our speakers surprise and inspire you! And don't forget to make new friends: there will be plenty of opportunities to meet people passionate about your favorite things. ❤️

Join us in Munich on November 10–11 for two days full of talks, workshops, showcases, networking, and fun!

DACHFest is a paid event, but diversity scholarships are available for people who belong to underrepresented groups in tech or cannot afford a ticket.

Website: https://dachfest.com
Twitter: https://twitter.com/dachfest
